Name: Bonus Morale
description: More morale is always preferable. These troops are less likely to flee or surrender in losing fight.

Name: Heroic
description: Heroes do not fear failure or death, but that does not mean they welcome it.

Name: Varied Training
description: The lack of standardised training for this unit make the troops' fighting ability wildly diverse.

Name: Zealous
description: Being zealous for one's belief can make soldier less susceptible to fear.

Name: Poor Morale
description: Either from poor training or by its nature, these soldiers have poorer morale making them unfit for prolong or serious engagement.

Name: Tough Painting
description: Orc Berserkers usually wear no armour at all and paint their naked body into battle. What littile known is that the paint materials used is so tough when harden that it can actually stop a sword or arrow.

Name: Impregnable Shield
description: One of the most basic equipment to keep one alive in a chaotic battle. Having one is almost always better than having none but having one that of superb quality is the best of all.

Name: Protective Fur
description: Some beastmen or creatures have furs thick enough to protect against some attack to a degree. Additionally, it can help against cold too.

Name: Charge Expert
description: Charge is one of the most powerful tactic in battles in the past that can decide the battle. Being well-versed in charging is never an disadvantage.

Name: Charge Defense Expert
description: Why settle for just defending when you can turn the enemies' charge into their own demise.

Name: Weapon Expert
description: Decades of perfection the weapon make these soldiers a pinnacle of all warriors.

Name: Evasive
description: These troops can dodge melee and range attack when fighting in loose formation.

Name: Arc Shot
description: Arc shot allows archers to shoot pass the obstacle to hit the target they aiming for. *This trait can be obtained from certain weapons.

Name: Agile Aims
description: These troops can shoot while moving and at moving enemy without penalty. A feat only the greatest archer can achieve. This property also help improve accuracy against moving target.

Name: Can Shoot While Moving
description: These troops can shoot while moving but with some accuracy penalty. Requires a lot of archery training but the result is undoubtedly beneficial.

Name: Concentrated Aims
description: The accuracy of these troops are not affected by morale (they still cannot shoot when broken).

Name: Concentrated Chant
description: These troops’ magic casting are not affected by morale (they still cannot cast magic when broken).

Name: Anti-Infantry
description: *This trait can be obtained from certain weapons.

Name: Anti-Flyer
description: What goes up must come down. These troops are specialised in combat against flyer enemies.

Name: Anti-Cavalry
description: These troops are specialised in combat against enemy cavalries. Bring an end to the age of cavalry one step at a time. *This trait can be obtained from certain weapons.

Name: Anti-Mage
description: These troops are specialised in combat against enemy mages. Not even the wisest wizards can survive this hunt.

Name: Anti-Machine
description: These troops are specialised in combat against enemy machines. Neither Iron or wood can not stop their attacks.

Name: Anti-Large
description: The bigger they are, the harder the fall. These troops are specialised in combat against large enemies.

Name: Anti-All
description: The destroyer of world. No man, beast nor machine can withstand this true might.

Name: Anti-Structure
description: Tear down the wall! No structure can withstand such strong force.

Name: Ignore Charge Defense
description: Rush of death and ruin. The world shall tremble upon this sight. These troops’ charge ignore charge defence entirely.

Name: Ignore Defense
description: Deadly to those unfortunate to face them in combat. These troops’ attack ignore defense entirely.

Name: Defiant Defense
description: Only the strongest force can take down unit. They will struggle to the end, and for every one man killed they will take down 10 enemies with them.

Name: Backstaber
description: These troops deal bonus damage to enemies with rear attack.

Name: Battle Master
description: These troops can fully attack enemies in all direction and suffer no defense penalty from being flank attack.

Name: Absolute Defense
description: The best defense is a good offense. It may be important to kill enemy to win the battle but it is more important to survive to win a war.

Name: Great Saint
description: The best of the best in the realm. These troops help nearby allies to be at maximum morale and cannot be decreased.

Name: No Hunger
description: These troops cannot get hungry which means they do not need food supply to maintain at all.

Name: Patriotic
description: It is the duty of every citizen to fight for the country they live in. These troops fight much better in friendly territory and require less upkeep.

Name: Siege Expert
description: No wall is safe from these soldiers! They can fight much better in siege combat. All defense +15% during siege, siege progression speed +50%.

Name: Unadvancable
description: These troops cannot gain experience from normal means.

Name: Hunger Instinct
description: Hunger is one of the most important factor for the aggressivity in most animal. If these troops are in hunger stage, they will fight much harder than usual to obtain the food which in this case is the enemy in front of them.

Name: Famed
description: These troops have been fighting through many battle and war, gaining them the fame it deserve. Increase some morale for allies nearby while reducing for enemies.

Name: Shield Expert
description: Survive to fight another day by improving your defense is never a bad idea.

Name: Crumble
description: Nothing last forever, even for an inanimate material creatures. Time has render these troops much less powerful compare to its former glory.

Name: Superb Flanker
description: These troops fight better against enemies from flanking position.

Name: Bandit Honour
description: The way of bandit usually is not appropriate to the code of honour. It must be extremely difficult and remarkable for one to uphold whatever honour vow they swear to.

Name: True Hero
description: Being true heroes, these troops has manifestly inspiring aura for nearby allies.

Name: Legendary Might
description: The might of the legends cannot be subdued. Beware the enemy for the death to come.

Name: Magical Weapon
description: These troops’ weapons have magic property which deals additional magic damage and can deals damage to Incorporeal enemies.

Name: Oblivious To Unexpected
description: These soldiers are so oblivious to unexpected events that they have no idea or plan to defend against them making it receive defense penalty from rear attack.

Name: Causes Fear
description: Only the brave can resist the fear, and those are the ones that die young.

Name: Causes Terror
description: Terror is in the mind until it manifest into reality in front of you. Fleeing is always an option.

Name: Inspires Hope
description: Instilling hope to your brother in arms is one of the greatest achievement one can perform in an army.

Name: Inspires Bravery
description: Bravery is a rare luxury in a place likes battlefield. To share such rarity to others is a noble deed indeed.

Name: Hope And Despair
description: A bringer of hope yet also a herald of calamity. Can it be the result of insanity?

Name: Glorious Appearance
description: These troops’ appearances are so dashing and inspiring that nearby allies will be in awe while leaving enemies in fear.

Name: Holy Defense
description: The blood and sins of the devil can veil one's mind. The lost sheep will then follow the true teaching.

Name: Vile Veil
description: There are none without sin and their sins will make them blind.

Name: Xenophobic Bunch
description: These troops loathe to fight together with soldiers or creatures from other race than themselves.

Name: Eyes Of Satiens
description: These troops suffer no range penalty and can shoot even further than usual.

Name: Farsight
description: Farsight reduce accuracy penalty from long range shooting and also make these troops see enemies’ projectiles earlier.

Name: No Range Penalty
description: Assured accuracy to eradicate enemy from any place.

Name: Long Range Accuracy
description: Death from afar, the end of chivalric era is near.

Name: Entertainer
description: Entertainment may look like it has no place in this hell. But it sure improve the soldiers’ morale.

Name: Cold Resistance
description: Cold resistant allows these troops to resist negative effect of cold terrain.

Name: Heat Resistance
description: Heat resistant allows these troops to resist negative effect of hot terrain.

Name: Fatigue Resistance
description: Fatigue is the natural consequence of any physical activity. It just come much later for some than the others.

Name: Swamp Dweller
description: Bonus combat and movement for these troops in swamp terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: Sylvan
description: Bonus combat and movement for these troops in forest terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: Blight Habitat
description: Bonus combat and movement for these troops in blight terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: Aquatic
description: Bonus combat and movement for these troops in water terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: Urban Guerrilla
description: Bonus combat and movement for these troops in urban terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: First Blood
description: These troops will deals bonus damage to enemies if they and the enemies both have no injury or death.

Name: Fervent Devotion
description: These troops fight better when being near the commander’s sub-unit.

Name: No Morale
description: These troops have no morale thus can not be motivated or broken.

Name: Knightly Valour
description: The valour of a knight is often a sight to behold for both enemy and friend. Often time, the flow of battle can change completely just from these knights’ presence.

Name: Thorny Armour
description: Unit that attack these troops in melee combat will also receive damage in return.

Name: Battle Preparation
description: These troops receive combat bonus when the stamina is at fresh level.

Name: Blessed
description: To the blessed heaven shall assist. The world is blight and the sky is clear.

Name: Cursed
description: A cursed being either by means of magic or nature, these troops will always be cursed and cannot be cured by normal means.

Name: Lucky
description: With luck on their side, surely no one can deny their destiny.

Name: Unlucky
description: Born under the wrong star or maybe some witches hold grudge against them, this unit usually fail at every task more than succeed.

Name: Fanatical Backstabbing
description: "Of course, it's personal because it's fun!" , Midjilipun, Big boss of Ritdukub clan in an exclusive interview with Chavu of Dina. Goblins really take joy in the art of backstabbing each other. Some can say it is a game or even a part of their nature for them.

Name: Tireless
description: Absolute killing machine! These troops' fatigue cannot be decreased making their combat effectiveness stay at the best condition for the whole fight.

Name: Unbreakable
description: Fleeing or surrendering is never an option for those with true honour and bravery. Death is a better option than dishonour.

Name: Savage Looter
description: These troops know well how to steal and plunder. While neither honourable or nobel, gold is essential even when running an army.

Name: Catcher Expert
description: A good enemy is not always a dead enemy. Prisoner of war often bring good ransom money especially when it come to captive noble.

Name: Marvelous Athletic
description: These troops being athletic superior makes them much more effective in long activity such as fighting.

Name: Iron Discipline
description: These troops receive further bonus effect from discipline.

Name: Infective Touch
description: Who can blame the unfortunates that want to spread misfortune to the others. The world is too bright for fake happiness.

Name: Mana Stealer
description: Every strike from these troops will sap away the mana of any enemy mage. Manaless mages make for nothing but useless baggages.

Name: Headtaker
description: These troops often decapitates enemies' head in combat as tokens. This will decrease their combat effectiveness by a bit but reduce enemy morale from damage further.

Name: Nasty Smell
description: These troops have disgusting stench that make anyone that not familiar with it want to throw up. every nearby sub-units receive combat penalty.

Name: Poison Blood
description: Completely immune to poison and dangerous to enemy when attacked. The ultimate evolution trait for revenge.

Name: Mirage Trickery
description: Not even the most accurate archer in the realm can shoot at mirage for the mind and reality are not the same.

Name: Martial Perfection
description: The life of devotion to martial perfection is not uncommon in the time of chaos. But rare still to see those who have perfected it.

Name: Forgetful
description: Forget order sometimes.

Name: Joyful Departure
description: Stemming from their peculiar tradition, these troops gain more morale when nearby ally sub-units are destroyed.

Name: High Jumper
description: These troops can jump quite high when attacking making them negate height penalty from critical by one level

Name: Unkillable
description: These troops cannot be killed by normal means.

Name: Lone Wolf
description: Rather fighting alone in the battlefield. The less friendly allies nearby, the more effective these troops become.

Name: Rotten Smell
description: Inducing vomit odour can cause great mental effect to the unfortunate victims.

Name: Wall Climbing
description: These troops can bypass wall easily. They do not require siege equipment in order to go above any wall but may suffer damage if the wall is filled with anti-climbing trap and do not receive any defense bonus from siege equipment.

Name: Hero Killer
description: These troops deal more damage to champion and hero grade enemies.

Name: Command Independent
description: These troops’ morale will not be affected by commander's death or retreat.

Name: Impetuous
description: Whether from pride or arrogance, these troops have tendency to follow order even less when the leader makes mistake or issue command they do not like.

Name: Hearty Competition
description: Being the elite of elite, these elite troops see battle as a game who kill the most enemy. The more they kill the higher their morale including nearby allies.

Name: Heroic Spirit
description: These troops are being led by a heroic spirit from the past. This make the troops in high spirit when follow their great hero into battle.

Name: Deathwish
description: These troops fight like it seeks death itself. Their morale can never be decreased.

Name: Troll Blood
description: Troll blood help its body to heal any wound it receives much faster than other creatures even during combat.

Name: Hope Crusher
description: When there is despair, there is hope. And it is the duty of these troops to crush that whatever tiny hope the enemies still have left.

Name: Merciless
description: These troops cannot capture running enemies as it always prefer killing them instead.

Name: Fragile Will
description: These troops will be affected by negative psychological effect even more than usual.

Name: Overwhelming Presence
description: These creatures’ appearance are so overwhelming that leave both friendly and enemy troops in fear and worry.

Name: Perfect Aims
description: Never a shot wasted when the enemies are lining up to be killed.

Name: Personal Escort
description: Trained to escort important person to safety, these troops will allow any leader they protect to survive for much longer in a chaotic battle.

Name: Domination Aura
description: When enemies becomes broken near these creatures, they will join these troops' side instead of freeing.

Name: Fire Being
description: Fire damage actually heal these creatures instead of damaging them.

Name: Water Being
description: Water damage actually heal these creatures instead of damaging them.

Name: Air Being
description: Air damage actually heal these creatures instead of damaging them.

Name: Earth Being
description: Earth damage actually heal these creatures instead of damaging them.

Name: Icy Being
description: Being made of ice, these creatures receive healing instead of damage from frozen status

Name: Penetration Shots
description: These troops’ range attacks are so powerful that they can penetrate enemy body and damage more than sub-unit per shot. They can also shot through weak obstacle and deals minor damage to major obstacle.

Name: Unholy Flesh
description: These troops can not be healed and will actually receive damage from healing magic.

Name: Field Medic
description: These troops can heal nearby allies when both are not in melee combat.

Name: Divine Presence
description: These troops are divine or considered to be divine by its followers. They will make every allies in the battlefield at maximum morale and cannot be broken.

Name: Forestry
description: No penalty in forest terrain for these troops.

Name: Seamate
description: Ahoy matey! Less movement and combat penalty on sea terrain for these troops.

Name: Mountaineer
description: Less movement and combat penalty from mountain terrain for these troops.

Name: Cave Crawling
description: Less movement and combat penalty in underground terrain for these troops.

Name: Pathfinder
description: Half Movement penalty in every terrain type and height for these troops.

Name: Night Vision
description: Hunter of the night. These troops suffer no vision loss at night at all.

Name: Pain Weakness
description: These troops are completely unfit for any direct battle! Any injury cause the them to fight less effectively.

Name: Cold Exposure
description: The lack of covering or wrong type of clothing can kill anyone just like the enemy in cold place. Warm up or be preserved forever.

Name: Heat Exposure
description: The cloth or armour this unit is wearing is not suitable for hot climate. The heat will render the body reaching mortality state eventually.

Name: Cowardice
description: Craven!, Useless! These troops are comprised of cowards and their morale will decrease even more from any factors.

Name: Treachery
description: Betrayal! These wretch troops are more likely to surrender and change side right away in dire situation. But, they will still try to flee instead if enemy force will not accept surrender.

Name: Sadism
description: These troops are addicted to inflicting pain and death. The more injury and death they inflict, the higher the morale.

Name: Masochism
description: These troops are addicted to receiving pain and death. The more injury and death they suffer, the higher the morale.

Name: Loves Fear
description: These troops actually love to feel fear. Being near anyone that causes or being affected by terror and fear regardless of side increase their morale.

Name: Seductive Charm
description: These troops’ appearance can charm enemies, making them become distracted and less effective in combat.

Name: Disgusting Taste
description: The worst taste of meat ever exist. No one will ever want to devour these creatures even if they have no taste buds.

Name: Rusty And Dirty
description: These troops’ weapons are covered with nasty rust making its less effective overall. However, their attacks can cause infection to injured enemies making them recover slower and harder to heal.

Name: Thrist For Blood
description: These troops thirst for blood, literally! The longer it fight the better its morale. It also suffers increasing morale penalty the longer it stay out of combat.

Name: Tainted Blood
description: Tainted blood is very dangerous if it come into contact with any untainted creature. Hence, melee combat against enemies with tainted blood is extremely inadvisable.

Name: Acid Blood
description: Bad news for everyone! Acid is raining down on whoever harm these creatures. Anyone that is affected by acid blood suffers combat penalty and also injury.

Name: Fantastic Beard
description: These troops have impressive beard that inspires all other dwarfs in the realm and battle.

Name: Mountain Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in mountain terrain.

Name: Hill Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in hill terrain.

Name: Forest Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in forest terrain.

Name: Cloud Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in sky.

Name: Desert Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in desert terrain.

Name: Snow Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in snow terrain.

Name: Water Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in water terrain.

Name: Plain Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in plain terrain.

Name: Swamp Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in swamp terrain.

Name: Urban Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in urban terrain.

Name: Blight Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in blight terrain.

Name: Underground Hiding
description: These troops can hide better in underground terrain.

Name: Night Stalking
description: These troops can hide better at night.

Name: Ambush Expert
description: These troops can hide in any terrain, nowhere is truly safe for the enemy.

Name: Champion's Crest
description: These troops are immortal and cannot be killed by any means, not even magic can harm them.

Name: Battle Frenzy
description: KILL! These berserkers can go into frenzy state similar to orc wrath that is even crazier than normal berserk.

Name: Scare Mount
description: These troops can cause mount to panic or scare, which reduce enemy cavalries’ combat effectiveness and morale.

Name: Fearless Mount
description: These troops’ mount cannot be panicked or broken and immune to Scare Mount.

Name: Human Killer
description: Human, they seem to be everywhere. So different, yet all so irritating. Time to make the world a better place by killing them all.

Name: Elf Murderer
description: Those damn arrogant gaze! Those damn annoying sneer! Darn elves think they are above every other races, let's show those sharp ears the death they deserve!

Name: Dwarf Exterminator
description: Short and stink! What good does dwarf bring to the world anyway? Useless sods they all are.

Name: Orc Destroyer
description: Orc Is nothing but a blight on civilisation.Its extinction will be another cornerstone of progress.

Name: Goblin Eradicator
description: Nasty little thing like this deserve to be eradicated. Kill them all and be rid of these pests for good or they will come back even more.

Name: Halfling Annihilator
description: Peace and love? Those who are not ready for war will never see peace.

Name: Animal Butcher
description: Look at those valuable fang and fur! Whoever deals the killing blow get the prize!

Name: Lizardman Eraser
description: Them scaly skins always are up to no good. We must erase them from the face of the earth so our children can live safely.

Name: Beastman Eliminator
description: Higher than mere beast but lower than man. These creatures deserve no better! The hunt is on!

Name: Giant Terminator
description: Big and brutish. Truly the greatest challenge for the greatest warrior.

Name: Dragon Slayer
description: Some say dragons were the sole ruler of the world in the age of origin, the true symbol of power. Not for us of course.

Name: Demon Banisher
description: How dare those vile demons invade our world! Go back to whatever the hell you all came from!

Name: Undead Liberator
description: Nothing less than blasphemy, the existance of these undeads. It is our duty to free them of these miserable state they are in.

Name: Fairy Crusher
description: Pure and innocence, is it? Those who say that obviously never meet the real one. It's always fun to crush annoying flies!

Name: Gremlin Bankrupter
description: To be the slave to money is make money your biggest weak point. Just make them lose all the money and watch them kill themselves over that.

Name: Wizard Hunters
description: "The unnatural of magecraft is too dangerous for any person to possess. Therefore, any person who practice the art of magic is punishable by death." The Absolute Law of Mortal Life, Fifth Act:Third Article

Name: Vindictive
description: Revenge is best served cold is what they often say. Well someone also like to have it hot!

Name: Animal Instinct
description: The basic of every animal is to survive. Based on that instinct, these creatures will flee much faster in losing fight but will give it all when it cannot escape and less likely to surrender.

Name: Phoenix Blood
description: Blood of immortal bird while not making one immunable to damage and disease, can help improve regenerative ability greatly while also allow the body to resurrect with enough energy.

Name: Incorporeal
description: "How can we kill this thing!?", An unknown soldier before being struck down. These troops cannot be damaged by normal weapon only from magic and magical weapon but also fight less effective.

Name: Oath Of The Eternal
description: Bound by the Eternal Oath, these soldiers will fight on even in death.

Name: Light Vision Intolerance
description: Blind by the light!, these troops cannot withstand the sight of sunlight making them unsuitable for daytime combat.

Name: Night Vision Intolerance
description: These troops cannot see well in the night at all which reducing their combat effectiveness greatly.

Name: Nocturnal
description: These troops fight better at night but worse at day.

Name: Willbreaker
description: Even the strongest will can be broken. These troops can make psychological resistance properties and abilities such as Strong Will of nearby enemies less effective.

Name: Adore Melody
description: These troops loves music dearly and will receive better combat bonus from music. However if the music stop, these troops will then receive combat penalty.

Name: Loathe Melody
description: These troops hate music and will receive combat penalty from music. If the music stop, these troops will receive combat bonus after.

Name: Salted Phase
description: The salted sea requires unconditional allegiance from those who wish to pass it. Only those with strongest will can survive in this unforgiving above the true abyss.

Name: Sorrow Of Battle
description: Woe for the world to see war and not peace. Our enemy too suffer the same fate as us.

Name: Smokey Wings At The Ground
description: When these troops suffer casualty, the Smokey Wings on the dead troops will drop to the ground. The smoke rising from the ground up will affect everyone without anti-smokey mask.

Name: Anti-Smokey Mask
description: These troops cannot be affected by Smokey ability.

Name: Strong Will
description: To have strong will is much harder to achieve than having strong body. Only few are so well trained to face against the unknown after all.

Name: Fullmoon Jubilance
description: The fateful day! These troops will fight firecely to the death to fulfill the prophecy.

Name: Halfmoon Preparation
description: There are no glory yet in battle before full moon, these troops will fight more reservely and more likely to retreat In losing fight.

Name: Crescentmoon Sacrifice
description: The rites must be made to hasten the arrival of the true moon! Sacrifices must be chosen!

Name: Darkmoon Melancholy
description: The darkest day! It is forbidden to die on this day at all cost.

Name: Bloodmoon Coming
description: The prophecy has been fulfilled! The gate of heaven is openned at last!

Name: Assassination
description: These troops can stay hidden while attacking if no enemy can spot it.

Name: Sniping
description: These troops can stay hidden while shooting.

Name: Invisible
description: These troops can stay hidden until fighting in melee.

Name: Full Awareness
description: These troops can detect enemy from any direction at all time.

Name: Partial Awareness
description: These troops can detect enemy from any direction when not fighting.

Name: True Sight
description: These troops can always detect any hidden enemy and trap.

Name: True Aims
description: These troops will always hit enemy regardless of range and bypass obstacle defense by half.The cowardly enemy cannot hide behind their shield anymore.

Name: Regenerating Limb
description: These troops can regenerate their lost limbs making them able to completely become combat ready again after resting.

Name: Regeneration
description: These troops can heal itself in time without needing medical assistant.

Name: Fast Regeneration
description: These troops can heal itself even in battle as long as it is not attacked.

Name: Limb Regeneration
description: These troops will not lose soldier count from injury after battle.
